3️⃣ Backend Setup
3.1 Create virtual environment & install dependencies
cd ~/KashiKartCiCd/backend
python3 -m venv .venv
source .venv/bin/activate
pip install -r requirements.txt
3.2 Backend .env

Create /backend/.env:

DATABASE_URL=postgresql://Stagging_Admin:YourPassword@staggin>
SECRET_KEY=a9a84d50e77b3fa27c69b4737373f436219b3d3b8e4e8b4616
ENCRYPTION_KEY=replace_with_a_secret_key
SMTP_USER=test@example.com
SMTP_PASSWORD=testpassword
SMTP_FROM_EMAIL=test@example.com
DEBUG=False

Replace <RDS_ENDPOINT> with your Aurora endpoint (from AWS RDS dashboard).

3.3 Backend systemd service

Create /etc/systemd/system/kashikart-backend.service:

[Unit]
Description=KashiKart FastAPI backend
After=network.target

[Service]
User=ubuntu
WorkingDirectory=/home/ubuntu/KashiKartCiCd/backend
Environment="PATH=/home/ubuntu/KashiKartCiCd/backend/.venv/bin"
ExecStart=/home/ubuntu/KashiKartCiCd/backend/.venv/bin/uvicorn app.main:app --host 0.0.0.0 --port 8000
Restart=always

[Install]
WantedBy=multi-user.target

Enable & start service:

sudo systemctl daemon-reload
sudo systemctl start kashikart-backend.service
sudo systemctl enable kashikart-backend.service
sudo systemctl status kashikart-backend.service

✅ Should show: Active: active (running)

4️⃣ Frontend Setup
4.1 Frontend .env

On your Mac, inside /frontend:

VITE_API_BASE_URL=http://<EC2_PUBLIC_IP>:8000

Replace <EC2_PUBLIC_IP> with the current public IP of your EC2 instance.

Optional: Use a shell script to automatically fetch the EC2 IP if you restart the server:

#!/bin/bash
# start-frontend.sh
EC2_IP=<EC2_PUBLIC_IP>
echo "VITE_API_BASE_URL=http://$EC2_IP:8000" > .env
npm run dev
4.2 Start frontend in background (Mac)

Use nohup or pm2 to run without blocking terminal:

# install pm2 if needed
npm install -g pm2

# start frontend
pm2 start npm --name frontend -- run dev
pm2 save  # keep it running after Mac restart
5️⃣ Backend Logs & Monitoring
Logs: sudo journalctl -u kashikart-backend.service -f
Restart service: sudo systemctl restart kashikart-backend.service
Enable at boot: sudo systemctl enable kashikart-backend.service
6️⃣ Notes for EC2 IP Changes
If you don’t want Elastic IP, after each restart of EC2, update .env in frontend:
VITE_API_BASE_URL=http://<NEW_EC2_IP>:8000
You can automate with a small shell script or pm2 ecosystem file.
7️⃣ Frontend ↔ Backend Connection
The only connection is via .env:
VITE_API_BASE_URL=http://<EC2_IP>:8000
All API calls in frontend use import.meta.env.VITE_API_BASE_URL.
8️⃣ Optional: Keep Scripts in Project Root

start-backend.sh (in root KashiKartCiCd):

#!/bin/bash
cd backend
source .venv/bin/activate
uvicorn app.main:app --host 0.0.0.0 --port 8000

start-frontend.sh (in root KashiKartCiCd):

#!/bin/bash
cd frontend
# Update API_BASE_URL with current EC2 IP
EC2_IP=<EC2_PUBLIC_IP>
echo "VITE_API_BASE_URL=http://$EC2_IP:8000" > .env
npm run dev

Make them executable:

chmod +x start-backend.sh start-frontend.sh

Now you can run:

./start-backend.sh  # on EC2
./start-frontend.sh # on Mac
