1️⃣ Backend .env.example

Create /backend/.env.example (do not commit real passwords)
# Database
DATABASE_URL=postgresql+asyncpg://<DB_USER>:<DB_PASSWORD>@<RDS_ENDPOINT>:5432/<DB_NAME>

# App
ENVIRONMENT=development
SECRET_KEY=<YOUR_SECRET_KEY>

Replace placeholders when deploying:
<DB_USER> = Kashikart
<DB_PASSWORD> = Kashikart1234
<RDS_ENDPOINT> = your Aurora RDS endpoint
<DB_NAME> = Kashikart

2️⃣ Frontend .env.example

Create /frontend/.env.example:

VITE_API_BASE_URL=http://<EC2_PUBLIC_IP>:8000

Replace <EC2_PUBLIC_IP> with your AWS EC2 public IP.

All frontend API calls will use:

import.meta.env.VITE_API_BASE_URL
3️⃣ start-backend.sh (root of project or backend folder)
#!/bin/bash
# Navigate to backend folder
cd backend || exit

# Activate virtual environment
source .venv/bin/activate

# Start FastAPI with uvicorn
uvicorn app.main:app --host 0.0.0.0 --port 8000

Make it executable:

chmod +x start-backend.sh

This script can also be used inside systemd if needed.

