5️⃣ start-frontend.sh (root of project or frontend folder)
#!/bin/bash
# Navigate to frontend folder
cd frontend || exit

# Automatically update .env with current EC2 IP
EC2_IP=<EC2_PUBLIC_IP>  # Update this whenever EC2 IP changes
echo "VITE_API_BASE_URL=http://$EC2_IP:8000" > .env

# Start frontend in dev mode
npm run dev

Make it executable:

chmod +x start-frontend.sh

Optional background run using pm2 (Mac):

npm install -g pm2
pm2 start ./start-frontend.sh --name frontend
pm2 save
6️⃣ Frontend ↔ Backend Connection
.env in frontend defines the API base URL.
Example in Vue/React:
fetch(`${import.meta.env.VITE_API_BASE_URL}/api/items`)

Only .env defines the connection between frontend and backend.

